Business Brief -- Dexter Corp.:
   Loss for the Fourth Quarter
   To Be Posted After Charge
In the year-earlier period, Dexter had net income of $9.4
million, or 39 cents a share, after a pretax gain of $7.1
million from product line sales and a pretax restructuring
charge of $5.1 million.
   The maker of specialty materials for industrial and
commercial products said income from operations in the 1991
fourth quarter declined to about $5.7 million, or 23 cents a
share, from $9.4 million, or 39 cents a share, the year
before. The company cited weak sales in the automotive,
electronics and construction markets.
   For all of 1991, Dexter said it expects to report a loss
of $6 million to $7 million, or about 25 cents to 30 cents a
share. In 1990, Dexter had net income of $42.2 million, or
$1.74 a share, on sales of $907.9 million.